A. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ilan et al., 2004" authorityName="Ilan et al." authorityYear="2004" box="[440,854,1740,1763]" class="Demospongiae" family="Niphatidae" genus="Amphimedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="chloros">
<emphasis box="[440,669,1740,1763]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Amphimedon chloros</emphasis>
Ilan et al., 2004
</taxonomicName>
, habit (scale bar = 1 cm); B. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ilan et al., 2004" authorityName="Ilan et al." authorityYear="2004" class="Demospongiae" family="Niphatidae" genus="Amphimedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="chloros">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Amphimedon chloros</emphasis>
Ilan et al., 2004
</taxonomicName>
, structure of the ectosomal skeleton showing the three­dimensional network of spicule tracts (scale bar = 0.5 mm); C–F. SEM­images of oxeas of 
